title: Merry Clappum Junction
creator: Arnold Kennedy
description: LibriVox recording of Merry Clappum Junction, or, The Strange Adventures of the New Zealand Express & a Boy: a quick train of thought by Arnold Kennedy (1853-1938). Read and sung by Ruth Golding. This is a jolly little book about a little boy, a dog, a train and a house. But not an ordinary train, oh no, and not an ordinary house either! And there are songs, too. The Preface is short, dull and only for the grown-ups. (Summary by Ruth Golding) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (30MB)
subject: librivox; audiobook; children; fantasy; train; music; song; the house that jack built; clapham junction;
